The paper presents a model for dynamic systems, which involves the creation and destruction of automata and the dynamic modification of their signatures. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category, which deals with formal methods and logical foundations of computer science. Additionally, the paper discusses operators for parallel composition, action hiding, action renaming, and behavioral subtyping, which are relevant to Programming Languages (cs.PL), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also mentions the modeling of mobility and hierarchical systems, which are relevant to Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL).
